    "properties": {
        "title": "Met Office Global Wave",	
    "description": "Met Office wave models are run to support marine safety and coastal hazards applications. The Global Wave model provides forecasts of sea-state characteristics based on predictions of two-dimensional (frequency-direction) wave spectra. The Met Office Global Wave model covers the global ocean from 80S to 80N. The Global Wave model is on a 25km spatial resolution at 50N. Hourly data are updated four times daily for forecast lead times up to 6 days ahead. Data are representative of wave conditions on scales of hours and 10s of kilometres and primarily recommended for use in water depths greater than 10m. Forcing for the wave model uses Met Office global Numerical Weather Prediction and it is recommended that Met Office data are used consistently when forecasting ocean and weather conditions across the marine boundary.",
